description*.en: $\textit{Magnetic Field Strength}$ is a vector quantity obtained at a given point by subtracting the magnetization $M$ from the magnetic flux density $B$ divided by the magnetic constant $\mu_0$. The magnetic field strength is related to the total current density $J_{tot}$ via: $\text{rot} H = J_{tot}$.
